==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Delta connection
<hw>Delta connection</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>One of the usual
forms or methods for connecting apparatus to a three-phase circuit, the
three corners of the delta or triangle, as diagrammatically represented,
being connected to the three wires of the supply circuit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delta current</ent>⟦br⟧
